I have TWO different clients of mine?one on the West side of Madison and one on the East side?who are looking for people who are passionate about Linux.  Check out the two positions below.
Most important: Docker or other container tools and Automation tools

To be successful as an Engineer 2, Systems you must have a keen understanding of the underlying technologies and have excitement in figuring out how things work end-to-end. You must be able to evangelize your thoughts to help drive innovative solutions to improve and streamline processes. This is an exciting place to work where you have the opportunity to interact with the highest level of engineering talent, constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower each other.
What you?ll be up to:
- Collaborating with architects, peers and engineering teams to develop and implement effective infrastructure solutions
- Testing, scheduling, and implementing software, hardware, configuration, and design changes to IT systems
- Identifying and responding to service incidents, investigating and resolving technical problems, and performing root cause analysis
- Monitoring and analyzing performance and availability of IT systems; conducting preventive maintenance to proactively identify and correct issues
- Performing task automation and implementing process improvements; recommending enhancements that result in increased quality and service
- Educating others regarding operational procedures and application and production standards
- Maintaining established service level agreements to manage customer expectations and quality standards; identifying opportunities for improvement
Qualifications:
Required:
- Must be presently authorized to work in the U.S. without a requirement for work authorization sponsorship by our company for this position now or in the future
- 3+ years of Linux Systems Engineering experience (Red Hat Preferred)
- 2+ years of experience with reading and writing scripts with languages such as Shell, Python, and/or Perl
- 2+ years of experience with automation tools such Puppet, Ansible, or Chef
- Experience with code management and deployment tools such as Jenkins, Rundeck, SVN, Git, or Artifactory
- Experience working with an incident management, work request, or project management tool such as Jira, Service Desk, Trello, or Asana
- Working knowledge of database concepts
- Must be committed to incorporating security into all decisions and daily job responsibilities
Preferred:
- Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Information Systems, Management Information Systems, or related field preferred
- 1+ years? experience working with cloud and/or virtualized environments such as AWS or Google Cloud
- Experience with log monitoring and evaluation tools such as Logz.io
- Experience with application monitoring tools such as Appdynamics
- Experience with virtualized lightweight container technologies such as Docker as well as container orchestration tools such as Rancher, Swarm, Kubernetes

The ideal candidate for this position is highly motivated with a passion for technology. You'll participate in the design, delivery and implementation of tools and applications critical to our customers. This candidate has the capacity to work with cross-functional operations and development teams throughout each phase of the product lifecycle.
Beacon Hill is an Equal Opportunity Employer that values the strength diversity brings to the workplace. Individuals with Disabilities and Protected Veterans are encouraged to apply.
Company Profile:

Beacon Hill Technologies, a premier National Information Technology Staffing Group, provides world class technology talent across all industries on a contract, direct (permanent), contract-to-direct and project basis.  Beacon Hill Technologies' dedicated team of recruiting and staffing experts consistently delivers quality IT professionals to solve our customers' technical and business needs.

Beacon Hill Technologies covers a broad spectrum of IT positions, including Project Management and Business Analysis, Programming/Development, Database, Infrastructure, Quality Assurance, Production/Support and ERP roles.

Learn more about Beacon Hill Staffing Group and our specialty divisions, Beacon Hill Associates, Beacon Hill Financial, Beacon Hill HR, Beacon Hill Legal, Beacon Hill Pharma and Beacon Hill Technologies by visiting
We look forward to working with you.

title: Vehicle Operator at Toyota - software / qa / dba / etc - job employment
description: QR Code Link to This Post
If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:

HireArt is looking to hire a Vehicle Operator to work at Toyota Research Institute's (TRI) Ann Arbor location on a contract basis. We're seeking motivated individuals with a passion for technology to join the Driving Operations Team.

You'll be responsible for TRI's autonomous vehicle platforms on various public and private roads obtaining data and fixing technical issues. As a specialist within Driving Operations, you're a valuable contributor, providing necessary feedback to our engineering team aimed at improving groundbreaking automated driving technology.

Toyota Research Institute (TRI) is working to build a future where everyone has the freedom to move, engage, and explore with a focus on reducing vehicle collisions, injuries, and fatalities. Join TRI's mission to improve the quality of human life through advances in artificial intelligence, automated driving, robotics and materials science. TRI is dedicated to building a world of "mobility for all" where everyone, regardless of age or ability, can live in harmony with technology to enjoy a better life.

Through innovations in AI, TRI aims to: 1) Develop vehicles incapable of causing a crash, regardless of the actions of the driver. 2) Develop technology for vehicles and robots to help people enjoy new levels of independence, access, and mobility. 3) Bring advanced mobility technology to market faster. 4) Discover new materials that will make drive batteries and hydrogen fuel cells smaller, lighter, less expensive and more powerful.

As a subsidiary of Toyota, TRI is fueled by a diverse and inclusive community of people who carry invaluable leadership, experience, and ideas from industry-leading companies. Over half of the technical team carries PhD degrees, and TRI is continually searching for the world's best talent ‒ people who are ready to define the new world of mobility!

TRI strives  to build a company that helps people thrive, achieve work life balance, and bring their best selves to work. You will have the opportunity to enjoy the best of both worlds ‒ a fun start up environment with brilliant people who enjoy solving tough problems and the financial backing to successfully achieve our goals. If you're passionate about working with smart people to make cars safer, enable the elderly to age in place, or design alternative fuel sources, TRI is the place for you.
If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:

Due to the nature of the position and daily inspections of the vehicle, this job often requires physical work including, but not limited to,  bending, stooping, and various operational tasks that may require lifting up to 50 lbs.  Additionally, the Vehicle Operations Specialist should expect to spend approximately four to six hours inside the vehicle on a daily basis.

This is a full-time (40 hours per week with possible overtime), ongoing, long-term contract position staffed via HireArt and based in Ann Arbor, MI. Compensation is hourly and paid training is provided. An offer of employment is contingent upon successful completion of the initial training. Occasional extended travel time may be required.

title: Vehicle Operator at Toyota - software / qa / dba / etc - job employment
description: QR Code Link to This Post
If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:

HireArt is looking to hire a Vehicle Operator to work at Toyota Research Institute's (TRI) Ann Arbor location on a contract basis. We're seeking motivated individuals with a passion for technology to join the Driving Operations Team.

You'll be responsible for TRI's autonomous vehicle platforms on various public and private roads obtaining data and fixing technical issues. As a specialist within Driving Operations, you're a valuable contributor, providing necessary feedback to our engineering team aimed at improving groundbreaking automated driving technology.

Toyota Research Institute (TRI) is working to build a future where everyone has the freedom to move, engage, and explore with a focus on reducing vehicle collisions, injuries, and fatalities. Join TRI's mission to improve the quality of human life through advances in artificial intelligence, automated driving, robotics and materials science. TRI is dedicated to building a world of "mobility for all" where everyone, regardless of age or ability, can live in harmony with technology to enjoy a better life.

Through innovations in AI, TRI aims to: 1) Develop vehicles incapable of causing a crash, regardless of the actions of the driver. 2) Develop technology for vehicles and robots to help people enjoy new levels of independence, access, and mobility. 3) Bring advanced mobility technology to market faster. 4) Discover new materials that will make drive batteries and hydrogen fuel cells smaller, lighter, less expensive and more powerful.

As a subsidiary of Toyota, TRI is fueled by a diverse and inclusive community of people who carry invaluable leadership, experience, and ideas from industry-leading companies. Over half of the technical team carries PhD degrees, and TRI is continually searching for the world's best talent ‒ people who are ready to define the new world of mobility!

TRI strives  to build a company that helps people thrive, achieve work life balance, and bring their best selves to work. You will have the opportunity to enjoy the best of both worlds ‒ a fun start up environment with brilliant people who enjoy solving tough problems and the financial backing to successfully achieve our goals. If you're passionate about working with smart people to make cars safer, enable the elderly to age in place, or design alternative fuel sources, TRI is the place for you.
If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:

Due to the nature of the position and daily inspections of the vehicle, this job often requires physical work including, but not limited to,  bending, stooping, and various operational tasks that may require lifting up to 50 lbs.  Additionally, the Vehicle Operations Specialist should expect to spend approximately four to six hours inside the vehicle on a daily basis.

This is a full-time (40 hours per week with possible overtime), ongoing, long-term contract position staffed via HireArt and based in Ann Arbor, MI. Compensation is hourly and paid training is provided. An offer of employment is contingent upon successful completion of the initial training. Occasional extended travel time may be required.
If you're interested in applying for the role, you can check it out here:

description:
QR Code Link to This Post



The County of Santa Barbara seeks an IT Programing Analyst I or II for the Social Services Department located in 
.  This position will provide IT security-related support to all Social Services staff, including setting up user permissions, cyber security, on-site server security, and oversight of the identification, containment and remediation of security breaches. This person will be valued by the organization for their ability to assess and identify vulnerabilities throughout the system, while making recommendations to remedy those vulnerabilities. The Programming Analyst, Security, protects the information of the most vulnerable population in the County and is a vital contributor to the success of the department. 



Our ideal candidate brings comprehensive knowledge of current IT security best practices and strong interpersonal skills to communicate and implement those practices across the Social Services Department. On a regular basis, this person adjusts staff entitlements, resolves application issues and reconfigures application access in tandem with State system upgrades. This position operates primarily in a Microsoft information technology environment and will utilize their IT technical savvy and emotional intelligence to build strong working relationships with both technical and non-technical clients. The incumbent will share creative ideas, investigate and remediate breaches, and continuously improve security standards.

 


	

	



	



	A California Class C Driver's License is required for both classifications prior to appointment, 


 IT Programming Analyst II
